Description: Floor and part of foot of Attic black-glazed stamped pottery stemless cup. Underside reserved with broad band at outside, band and circle at centre. Elaborate impressed decoration on inside: cross-hatching around tongues, around eight linked palmettes emerging from circlet of tongues. Incised inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 571)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1669)
